          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Measure Customer Satisfaction with In-App CSAT Surveys",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Customer Satisfaction Score (CSAT) surveys are the bread and butter of support and product teams. The classic question — *\"How satisfied were you with your experience?\"* — gives you a number you can track week over week.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What makes Survicate stand out here is the ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "in-app delivery",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ". Instead of sending a follow-up email that lands in a crowded inbox two days later, you trigger the survey directly inside your web or mobile app the moment a user completes an action: finishing onboarding, closing a support chat, or hitting a usage milestone.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How teams use it:",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A SaaS support team sets a Survicate CSAT survey to appear after every live chat session. Responses flow into Intercom, and the support lead reviews detractors within the hour.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "An e-commerce company triggers a one-question CSAT popup after checkout. Average scores are segmented by device type, revealing that mobile checkout satisfaction lags 12 points behind desktop — a signal that kicks off a UX sprint.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Because Survicate supports ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "multilingual surveys",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " out of the box, teams running global products don't need separate survey builds for each locale. You write one survey, add translations, and the platform auto-delivers the right version based on the user's browser language.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
