      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Net Promoter Score remains the single most common executive-level metric for customer loyalty. Yet most teams still run it poorly — a quarterly email blast that gets a 4% response rate and sits in a spreadsheet no one opens.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Survicate changes that by letting you run ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "relationship NPS",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " (periodic check-ins) and ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "transactional NPS",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " (triggered after specific events) across multiple channels from one dashboard. You can embed an NPS survey in-app on a Monday, send a follow-up email to passives on Wednesday, and push promoter data to your CRM for a referral campaign by Friday.",
